ith low threshold; circuit breaker closed but summarize function failing","timestamp":"2026-06-27T16:44:11.433Z","title":"Agent memory consolidation and health check","type":"command_run"},"obs_mqwlbd6p_7b9fd56798e8":{"concepts":["observation consolidation","concept-based grouping","LLM rate limiting","project-scoped operations","cross-project data isolation","batch query optimization","memory deduplication"],"confidence":1,"facts":["registerConsolidateFunction registers mem::consolidate function with SDK","Filters sessions by project if provided, defaults to minObservations of 10","Batches session queries in chunks of 10 to fetch CompressedObservations","Filters observations by title existence and importance >= 5","Groups observations by concept (lowercase keys) requiring minimum 3 per group","Caps LLM calls at 10 per consolidation run with 30-second timeout per call","Sorts concept groups by observation count descending, takes top 8 per concept","Uses parseMemoryXml to parse LLM compress() response output","Includes project scoping guard to prevent cross-project memory corruption when consolidating","Generates CONSOLIDATION_SYSTEM prompt with concept context and formatted observations"],"files":["/Users/gwang/github_repo/agentmemory/src/functions/consolidate.ts"],"id":"obs_mqwlbd6p_7b9fd56798e8","importance":8,"narrative":"The consolidate.ts file implements a memory consolidation system that batches session queries, groups high-importance observations by concept, and uses LLM compression with rate limiting to generate reusable memory entries. The code includes explicit project-scoping logic to prevent accidental cross-project corruption when unscoped consolidation runs encounter identically-titled memories across different projects.","sessionId":"7058b98f-8167-4834-a075-52b0181a8140","subtitle":"Memory consolidation engine with concept grouping and LLM compression","timestamp":"2026-06-27T16:44:30.685Z","title":"Read consolidate.ts function registration and LLM co