ion result: 2 memories consolidated (compressed)","Total observations processed: 753","After consolidation: 3 memories in system","No errors in server log during consolidation process","Consolidation completed within 120 second timeout"],"files":["/private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-gwang-github-repo-agentmemory/7058b98f-8167-4834-a075-52b0181a8140/scratchpad/am-server.log"],"id":"obs_mqwlnmhd_90bb8b9547da","importance":6,"narrative":"A consolidation operation was triggered on the agentmemory server with a minObservations threshold of 3. The system successfully compressed 753 observations, resulting in 2 consolidated memories. The memory count increased from 1 to 3 after consolidation, indicating new memories were created from the compressed observations. No errors or parsing issues were detected in the server logs during the operation.","sessionId":"7058b98f-8167-4834-a075-52b0181a8140","subtitle":"Triggered consolidation with minObservations=3 threshold","timestamp":"2026-06-27T16:54:02.606Z","title":"Memory consolidation test: 753 observations consolidated to 3 memories","type":"command_run"},"obs_mqwlnvqu_61848820caa3":{"concepts":["memory service API","JSON parsing error","HTTP response truncation","OpenSpec workflow"],"confidence":1,"facts":["Command targeted localhost:3111/agentmemory/memories endpoint with latest=true&limit=100 parameters","Python3 inline script attempted to parse JSON and format memory records","Error occurred at JSON parsing stage with SyntaxError on line 1","Response from endpoint appears to have been truncated or malformed, breaking JSON syntax at the title field","The memory being retrieved concerns OpenSpec workflow with concepts: opsx-workflow, openspec, opsx-explore, opsx-propose, opsx-apply, opsx-archive, development-workflow"],"files":["openspec/","docs/superpowers/specs/","docs/log/"],"id":"obs_mqwlnvqu_61848820caa3","importance":4,"narrative":"The curl command successfully connected to the memory service but the piped Python JSON parser failed to process the response. The JSON appears truncated mid-field (at a title value), suggesting either the HTTP response was incomplete or there's a character encoding/formatting issue in the memory service's output. This prevented inspection of the agent's current memory state.","sessionId":"7058b98f-8167-4834-a075-52b0181a8140","subtitle":"Bash command attempting to fetch and format agent memories","timestamp":"2026-06-27T16:54:14.612Z","title":"Memory retrieval script failed with JSON parsing error","type":"error"},"obs_mqwlo5t5_075d9a877a01":{"concepts":["circuit breaker pattern","memory consolidation pipeline","observation taxonomy","concept clustering","LLM compression pipeline","summarize function failure","distillation pipeline","OpenSpec workflow"],"confidence":1,"facts":["Total memories in system: 3","Memory 1: OpenSpec workflow documentation (type: workflow, strength: 7, created 2026-06-27T13:07:11.607Z)","Memory 2: Circuit Breaker Pattern Recognition (type: pattern, strength: 7, created 2026-06-27T16:53:57.420Z) - 752 audited observations, summarize function: 119 fails/0 successes","Memory 3: Memory consolidation pipeline blocked (type: bug, strength: 9, created 2026-06-27T16:54:01.465Z) - 742 observations, 119/119 summarize failures, 0% success rate","Circuit breaker pattern is only concept cluster meeting consolidation thresholds (3+ occurrences)","Distillation pipeline non-functional despite operational infrastructure"],"files":["/private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-gwang-github-repo-agentmemory/7058b98f-8167-4834-a075-52b0181a8140/scratchpad/mems.json"],"id":"obs_mqwlo5t5_075d9a877a01","importance":9,"narrative":"The agent successfully queried the AgentMemory service at localhost:3111 and retrieved 3 stored memories spanning workflow documentation, pattern recognition, and a critical bug report. The most recent memory (strength: 9, highest priority) indicates the memory consolidation pipeline is completely broken - the summarize function has a 0% success rate across 119 attempts, blocking the entire compression/distillation mechanism despite adequate observation volume (742 records). This is a critical architectural failure affecting memory compression capability.","sessionId":"7058b98f-8167-4834-a075-52b0181a8140","subtitle":"Queried localhost:3111 agentmemory service and parsed 3 stored memories","timestamp":"2026-06-27T16:54:27.655Z","title":"Agent Memory System State Audit - 3 Critical Memories Retrieved","type":"command_run"},"obs_mqwloowo_55682829ed16":{"concepts":["subagent lifecycle management","task delegation completion"],"confidence":0.9,"facts":["Subagent stopped at 2026-06-27T16:54:52.407Z","No error state indicated in stop signal"],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwloowo_55682829ed16","importance":3,"narrative":"A subagent process has completed execution and stopped. This marks the end of a delegated task or parallel operation within the current agent workflow.","sessionId":"7058b98f-8167-4834-a075-52b0181a8140","subtitle":"Subagent process stopped","timestamp":"2026-06-27T16:54:52.407Z","title":"Subagent execution completed","type":"subagent"},"obs_mqwluydn_a0e8337ffe62":{"concepts":["AGENTMEMORY_AUTO_COMPRESS configuration","live coding memory storage","agent memory persistence"],"confidence":1,"facts":["User is asking about AGENTMEMORY_AUTO_COMPRESS configuration flag","Specific concern: whether information can be stored during live coding when auto_compress is set to false","User is questioning the relationship between auto-compression and memory storage capability"],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwluydn_a0e8337ffe62","importance":4,"narrative":"The user is inquiring about the behavior of the agent memory system when auto-compression is disabled. They want to know if setting AGENTMEMORY_AUTO_COMPRESS to false impacts the ability to store information during live coding sessions, suggesting they may be considering disabling auto-compression but want to ensure memory persistence still works.","sessionId":"7058b98f-8167-4834-a075-52b0181a8140","subtitle":"User asking about memory persistence behavior with auto-compress disabled","timestamp":"2026-06-27T16:59:44.616Z","title":"Question about AGENTMEMORY_AUTO_COMPRESS and live coding storage","type":"conversation"},"obs_mqwlv9d4_2dff98d15c22":{"concepts":["zero-LLM synthetic compression","environment variable feature gating","hybrid compression strategy (cost vs quality tradeoff)","synthetic sessionId for memory scope isolation","API token cost awareness"],"confidence":1,"facts":["AUTO_COMPRESS is a boolean environment variable (AGENTMEMORY_AUTO_COMPRESS=true/false) defined in src/config.ts:385-386","When AUTO_COMPRESS=false (default), observations use zero-LLM synthetic compression for indexing/search without API token cost","When AUTO_COMPRESS=true, every PostToolUse observation is sent to LLM provider for richer summaries, incurring token costs proportional to tool-use frequency (issue #138)","isAutoCompressEnabled() is imported and checked in src/index.ts:277 and src/triggers/api.ts:210","A synthetic sessionId (\"memory\" or fallback to first real sessionId) is used for zero-LLM compression path in KV.memories scope","Search context kinds include \"synthetic\" alongside \"memory\" and \"observation\" (src/functions/search.ts)","MCP tools registry at src/mcp/tools-registry.ts:652 exposes LLM-powered crystal digest compression as a user-callable tool"],"files":["src/config.ts","src/index.ts","src/triggers/api.ts","src/mcp/tools-registry.ts","src/state/memory-utils.ts","src/state/hybrid-search.ts","src/functions/search.ts"],"id":"obs_mqwlv9d4_2dff98d15c22","importance":8,"narrative":"The agent memory system implements a dual compression strategy: by default (AUTO_COMPRESS=false), observations are indexed via synthetic zero-LLM compression to avoid API costs while maintaining searchability; users can opt-in (AUTO_COMPRESS=true) for richer LLM-generated summaries at the cost of API token consumption. The feature is gated by an environment variable checked at initialization and affects whether observations flow through the LLM provider or synthetic indexing pipeline.","sessionId":"7058b98f-8167-4834-a075-52b0181a8140","subtitle":"Grep search identifying where AUTO_COMPRESS env var is read and what compression modes it gates","timestamp":"2026-06-27T16:59:58.855Z","title":"AUTO_COMPRESS feature gates and zero-LLM synthetic compression path","type":"command_run"},"obs_mqwlvw4t_6543f47f4f82":{"concepts":["subagent lifecycle management","process termination","task delegation"],"confidence":0.9,"facts":["Subagent process has stopped","Timestamp indicates completion at 2026-06-27T17:00:28.365Z"],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwlvw4t_6543f47f4f82","importance":4,"narrative":"A subagent execution has concluded. This marks the end of a delegated task or parallel processing operation. The timing and context of the stop event should be cross-referenced with any prior subagent_start events to determine task completion status.","sessionId":"7058b98f-8167-4834-a075-52b0181a8140","subtitle":"Process termination event","timestamp":"2026-06-27T17:00:28.365Z","title":"Subagent execution completed","type":"subagent"},"obs_mqwm0dul_cefc407e8885":{"concepts":["BM25 full-text search","local vector embeddings","hybrid search (BM25 + vector)","API-independent retrieval"],"confidence":1,"facts":["Grep for AUTO_COMPRESS and LLM provider calls in context.ts, enrich.ts, search.ts returned only vLLM endpoint comments (lines 133, 209), not actual dependencies","Search.ts imports VectorIndex and EmbeddingProvider locally","Retrieval path does NOT call LLM or AUTO_COMPRESS functionality","BM25 and vector embedding search uses local implementations with no API key requirements"],"files":["src/functions/search.ts","src/functions/context.ts","src/functions/enrich.ts","src/state/vector-index.js","src/types.js"],"id":"obs_mqwm0dul_cefc407e8885","importance":7,"narrative":"Investigation confirmed that the retrieval/injection path in search.ts is completely independent from AUTO_COMPRESS and LLM provider calls. The grep results show only incidental mentions of vLLM in comments about batching optimization, not functional dependencies. The search function implements hybrid BM25 + local embedding vector search, making it suitable for scenarios without external API access.","sessionId":"7058b98f-8167-4834-a075-52b0181a8140","subtitle":"Search function uses local BM25 + embeddings, no API calls required","timestamp":"2026-06-27T17:03:57.949Z","title":"Verified retrieval path independence from LLM/compression","type":"command_run"},"obs_mqwm0h3n_ac562089ab8f":{"concepts":["agent memory context injection","PreToolUse enrichment pipeline","API parameter validation","session management"],"confidence":1,"facts":["POST request to http://localhost:3111/agentmemory/context with query \"consolidation pipeline summarize\" and limit=3","Request failed with error: \"sessionId and project are required strings\"","API expects sessionId and project as mandatory string parameters in request body","Response returned JSON error object instead of context data","Command executed with 8-second timeout and output saved to scratchpad ctx.json"],"files":["/private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-gwang-github-repo-agentmemory/7058b98f-8167-4834-a075-52b0181a8140/scratchpad/ctx.json"],"id":"obs_mqwm0h3n_ac562089ab8f","importance":5,"narrative":"An API call to the agent memory context endpoint was attempted to simulate what context would be injected during PreToolUse enrichment. The request failed because required sessionId and project parameters were missing from the payload. This indicates the memory API has strict validation for session and project identification before returning context results.","sessionId":"7058b98f-8167-4834-a075-52b0181a8140","subtitle":"PreToolUse enrichment path query to localhost:3111","timestamp":"2026-06-27T17:04:02.162Z","title":"Memory context API validation test","type":"command_run"},"obs_mqwm0ozx_49114d2ba0ce":{"concepts":["agentmemory context injection","session-based memory retrieval","consolidation pipeline","circuit breaker pattern","context window management"],"confidence":1,"facts":["Session ID: demo_mqvpoq0a_af0da424bb55","Project: accounting-firm","Query: \"consolidation pipeline summarize circuit breaker\"","Context size: 5627 characters","agentmemory server running on localhost:3111","Retrieved from session 92617014 (2026-06-27T15:44:34.903Z)","Output file: /private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-gwang-github-repo-agentmemory/7058b98f-8167-4834-a075-52b0181a8140/scratchpad/ctx.json","Previous interactions include: prompt_submit about hook test, agentmemory-hooks skill execution, server health check, hooks.json file read"],"files":["/private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-gwang-github-repo-agentmemory/7058b98f-8167-4834-a075-52b0181a8140/scratchpad/ctx.json","/Users/gwang/.claude/plugins/cache/agentmemory/agentmemory/0.9.27/hooks/hooks.json"],"id":"obs_mqwm0ozx_49114d2ba0ce","importance":6,"narrative":"The agent queried the agentmemory context API to retrieve relevant historical information about consolidation pipeline and circuit breaker patterns for the accounting-firm project. The context injection system returned 5627 characters of structured session history including previous conversations and file operations, which gets prepended to Claude's context window. This enables the agent to maintain continuity across tool interactions.","sessionId":"7058b98f-8167-4834-a075-52b0181a8140","subtitle":"Retrieved 5627-char injected context from accounting-firm project","timestamp":"2026-06-27T17:04:12.396Z","title":"Query agentmemory context for consolidation pipeline","type":"command_run"},"obs_mqwm2zhy_ed05e64b5ee6":{"concepts":["Memory storage mechanism","UI state vs data persistence","Memory visibility settings"],"confidence":1,"facts":["User observed that the \"Memories\" tab shows as empty when a setting is turned off","User is questioning where stored information is being kept if not visible in the Memories tab","User wants to know how to access or check stored information"],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwm2zhy_ed05e64b5ee6","importance":4,"narrative":"The user is investigating the relationship between memory storage and UI visibility. They noticed the Memories tab appears empty under certain conditions and are trying to understand the backend storage mechanismвЂ”specifically, whether information is still being stored when the UI doesn't display it, and how they can verify or access it.","sessionId":"7058b98f-8167-4834-a075-52b0181a8140","subtitle":"Clarification on where past information is stored when Memories tab appears empty","timestamp":"2026-06-27T17:05:59.316Z","title":"User asking about memory storage location and visibility","type":"conversation"},"obs_mqwm3eex_b87546bc5864":{"concepts":["lazy loading pattern with loaded flags","view-specific state management","observations as fundamental data unit","pagination and filtering across views","semantic memory consolidation"],"confidence":1,"facts":["Three main dashboard view containers: view-timeline, view-sessions, view-activity (lines 1014-1017)","Timeline view state tracks: loaded flag, observations array, sessionId, minImportance, pagination (page/pageSize)","Activity view state tracks: loaded flag, observations array, sessions array, typeFilter","Each view has dedicated loader function: loadTimeline(), loadSessions(), loadActivity() triggered by case statements (lines 1330-1336)","Timeline view calls loadObservations() when sessionId is set (line 2548)","Observations are core data unit across all three views, consolidated into semantic memories over time"],"files":["src/viewer/index.html"],"id":"obs_mqwm3eex_b87546bc5864","importance":6,"narrative":"The viewer dashboard has three distinct tabs (timeline, sessions, activity) that all render observations but with different state management and filtering approaches. Timeline focuses on sequential observations within a session, sessions shows aggregated data per session, and activity provides a type-filtered view. Each has lazy-loaded state with observations arrays that feed the rendering logic.","sessionId":"7058b98f-8167-4834-a075-52b0181a8140","subtitle":"Three views (timeline, sessions, activity) load observations differently","timestamp":"2026-06-27T17:06:18.649Z","title":"Dashboard tabs rendering observations structure","type":"discovery"},"obs_mqwm3hu4_1ad0b1f9b671":{"concepts":["agent memory state store","observation persistence","REST API endpoint","session management"],"confidence":1,"facts":["26 observation files stored in /Users/gwang/Develop/accounting-firm/data/state_store.db/","Total disk usage: 7.1M for state_store.db directory","Active session ID: demo_mqvpoq0a_af0da424bb55","Session contains 3 observations: 2 file_write operations and 1 command_run","REST API endpoint confirmed working at http://localhost:3111/agentmemory/"],"files":["/Users/gwang/Develop/accounting-firm/data/state_store.db/"],"id":"obs_mqwm3hu4_1ad0b1f9b671","importance":5,"narrative":"Agent memory state store inspection revealed 26 persisted observation files totaling 7.1M on disk. REST API query of active session demo_mqvpoq0a_af0da424bb55 returned 3 observations (2 file writes, 1 bash command). This validates both filesystem persistence and REST API accessibility of the agent memory compression system.","sessionId":"7058b98f-8167-4834-a075-52b0181a8140","subtitle":"Verified agent memory state store via filesystem and REST API","timestamp":"2026-06-27T17:06:23.082Z","title":"Inspected observation storage: 26 files, 7.1M total, 3 observations in active session","type":"command_run"},"obs_mqwm3zwl_0c18b8d588a0":{"concepts":["subagent lifecycle management","task delegation","async operation completion"],"confidence":0.9,"facts":["Subagent execution ended at 2026-06-27T17:06:46.500Z","Hook triggered: subagent_stop"],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwm3zwl_0c18b8d588a0","importance":3,"narrative":"A subagent task has completed or been terminated. This marks the end of a delegated subtask within the larger coding operation. The timing and completion status should be noted for task orchestration tracking.","sessionId":"7058b98f-8167-4834-a075-52b0181a8140","subtitle":"Subagent task completion or termination event","timestamp":"2026-06-27T17:06:46.500Z","title":"Subagent execution stopped","type":"subagent"},"obs_mqwm5px1_7d738fbfd331":{"concepts":["token budget allocation","project-scoped filtering and ranking","multiplicative scoring with priority multipliers","slice-based pagination limits","importance threshold filtering","recency tracking with reduce()"],"confidence":1,"facts":["Token budget parameter passed via data.budget with fallback to tokenBudget","ProjectProfile content sliced to 8 items for main profile, 5 for secondary content","Lessons filtered by project match and deletion status, sorted by confidence with 1.5x multiplier for project-scoped lessons","Lessons limited to top 10 via .slice(0, 10)","Sessions filtered by project match and sessionId exclusion, sorted, limited to 10","Observations filtered by importance >= 5 threshold, sorted by importance descending, limited to 5","estimateTokens() function computes token consumption for each content block","mostRecent timestamp tracked via reduce() across relevantLessons","Ranking uses multiplicative scoring: (projectMatch ? 1.5 : 1) * confidence"],"files":["src/functions/context.ts"],"id":"obs_mqwm5px1_7d738fbfd331","importance":7,"narrative":"The context.ts SessionStart injection implements multi-stage filtering and ranking to select memory items within a token budget. It uses project-scoped priority (1.5x confidence multiplier), importance thresholds, and fixed slice limits (8/5/10/5) to balance content diversity while respecting token constraints. Each content block is individually token-estimated and ranked.","sessionId":"7058b98f-8167-4834-a075-52b0181a8140","subtitle":"Extracted token budget, sorting, filtering, and slicing patterns","timestamp":"2026-06-27T17:08:06.867Z","title":"Analyzed context.ts SessionStart injection selection logic","type":"command_run"},"obs_mqwm5qnd_5e4a46d10dd6":{"concepts":["PreToolUse injection hook","Memory selection by file relevance","Project-scoped memory filtering","Query construction from file paths","Multi-source parallel context fetching","Bidirectional string inclusion matching","Context length budgeting"],"confidence":1,"facts":["enrich.ts implements memory selection via query construction from files and optional terms","Search queries are built by extracting filenames and combining with user-provided terms","Search limit is hardcoded to 5 results per query call","Memory filtering guards against cross-project contamination unless both project fields are undefined","Results are sorted and sliced to top 3 observations before injection","File matching uses bidirectional inclusion checks: f.includes(df) || df.includes(f)","Final context is capped at MAX_CONTEXT_LENGTH via slice operation","Three parallel data sources are fetched: fileContext, searchResult, and bugMemories"],"files":["src/functions/enrich.ts"],"id":"obs_mqwm5qnd_5e4a46d10dd6","importance":7,"narrative":"The enrich.ts PreToolUse hook implements a multi-stage memory enrichment pipeline. It constructs search queries from affected file paths and optional search terms, executes searches with a limit of 5 results, filters memories by project scope and file relevance, ranks results, and injects the top 3 observations into the agent context. The context injection includes guards against cross-project memory leakage while allowing unscoped memories to pass through.","sessionId":"7058b98f-8167-4834-a075-52b0181a8140","subtitle":"PreToolUse injection memory enrichment mechanism","timestamp":"2026-06-27T17:08:07.816Z","title":"Grep analysis of enrich.ts selection and ranking logic","type":"command_run"},"obs_mqwm7a7a_0b232f979d11":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"